# Context

Residual learning: train the model to predict `torAct[t] - torEst[t]` instead of `torAct[t]` directly. At inference, `pred = torEst[t] + model_output`. This is a skip connection from torEst to the output, motivated by torEst's RMSE of 19.8 Nm against torAct (Test 1) — a poor standalone predictor but a reasonable starting point the NN can correct.

Per-profile analysis (your manual 4-profile evaluation) revealed that control mode dominates performance: tStep GRU RMSE 0.37 Nm, PLC GRU RMSE 67.25 Nm. This reframes the residual-learning experiment: on torque-controlled profiles (kd=0) torEst ≈ torDes + small_rotor_term, so `torAct - torEst` is primarily the rotor-inertia and friction residual. On position-generated velocity-controlled profiles (kd=18) torEst contains the full PD output, so `torAct - torEst` is a more complex quantity that may be harder or easier to learn depending on how well torEst tracks torAct during ringing events.

The residual target might help asymmetrically across profiles. Evaluation must therefore be per-profile, not aggregate-only.

# Task

1. Add config flag `RESIDUAL_TARGET = True` (default False to preserve v1 behavior).

2. When RESIDUAL_TARGET=True:
   - Training target becomes `torAct[t] - torEst[t]` at the final window timestep.
   - Target scaler is fit on training-set residuals.
   - Loss is MSE on normalized residuals.
   - Inference reconstructs: `pred_torque = scaler_y.inverse_transform(model_output) + torEst[t]`.
   - Metrics are always reported on reconstructed torque, not on the residual. This is non-negotiable — the comparison to v1 must be apples-to-apples.

3. Log residual-target distribution statistics (mean, std, skew, kurtosis, min, max) on the training set before training starts. If the residual distribution has extreme skew or kurtosis, flag it — MSE may be poorly suited and Huber may be needed as a follow-up.

4. Retrain MLP and GRU with RESIDUAL_TARGET=True at SEQ_LEN=30. Same hyperparameters as v1. Same seeds. Save to `checkpoints/residual/`.

5. Evaluate on the full test set AND per-profile (stratified by filename as in Prompt 11).

6. Run Test 4 (model agreement) on the residual-trained models: if the residual framing breaks the v1 architecture-convergence (corr(pred_mlp, pred_gru) < 0.995), it indicates the two models now explore the residual space independently.

